data.title: All The Monkees Songs Sung By Michael Nesmith
data.meta_description:
This youtube playlist provides a nice list except that #14 & #15 have been deleted.

Is there a Monkee detective out there who can work out what those...
data.text:
Here's the songs included on the playlist:

1 Papa Gene's Blues From The Monkees

2 Sweet Young Thing From The Monkees

3 All The King's Horses From The Monkees (Deluxe)

4 The Kind of Girl I Could Love (Original Stereo Version) (2006 Remaster) From More of The Monkees

5 You Told Me (2007 Remaster) From Headquarters

6 You Just May Be The One (2007 Remastered Version) From Headquarters

7 Sunny Girlfriend (2007 Remastered Version) From Headquarters

8 The Girl I Knew Somewhere (First Recorded Version) (Alternate Mono Mix) From Headquarters

9 Salesman (2007 Remastered Version) From Pisces, Aquarius, Capricorn & Jones Ltd.

10 The Door Into Summer (2007 Remastered Version) From Pisces, Aquarius, Capricorn & Jones Ltd.

11 Love Is Only Sleeping (2007 Remaster) From Pisces, Aquarius, Capricorn & Jones Ltd.

14

23 Good Clean Fun From The Monkees Present: Micky, David & Michael

24 Never Tell a Woman Yes From The Monkees Present: Micky, David & Michael

25 Listen to the Band (Alternate Stereo Mix) From The Monkees Present: Micky, David & Michael

27 Me & Magdalena From Good Times!

28 Birth of an Accidental Hipster From Good Times!

29 I Know What I Know From Good Times!

The playlist is purported to be chronological.

So the missing tracks are likely from Head. Daddy's Song & Ditty Diego - War Chant?

And I’ll take the raw energy of the live version, from the film, with the four Monkees playing, over any of the studio takes.

From the HEAD sessions there’s also an alternate take of Mike singing “Daddy’s Song,” which of course Davy ultimately sang for the film and soundtrack. But Mike vocal’s been included as a bonus track with HEAD reissues.

But one of those missing tracks has to be “Tapioca Tundra,” and I’d bet it’s the alternate take of “Auntie’s” as previously mentioned.

Plenty more alternate takes and unreleased (At the time) songs that Mike sang: “I Don’t Think You Know Me,” “Of You,” “Propinquity,” “Nine Times Blue,” “Some of Shelly’s Blues,” “If I Ever Get to Saginaw Again,” “Down the Highway,” “Angel Band,” “Hollywood,” “Carlisle Wheeling,” “The Crippled Lion” and probably more I’m forgetting.

That’s the CD that also has the instrumental coda tacked back on to “Porpoise Song.”

I’d like to snag that CD for that reason alone. Never liked how the original soundtrack ends the song early. Rhino’s LP and cassette from 1986 added the coda, but never on CD except for that UK edition.
